<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-2036] Thrift gem warns about class variable access from top level</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-2036</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Steps:&lt;br/&gt;
1. Generate thrift client and server from thrift definition file.&lt;br/&gt;
2. Require thrift client or server in a ruby script.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The following warning is printed:&lt;br/&gt;
2.0.0-p195/lib/ruby/gems/2.0.0/gems/thrift-0.9.0/lib/thrift/protocol/json_protocol.rb:21: warning: class variable access from toplevel&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here is a patch from the Evernote SDK: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/evernote/evernote-sdk-ruby/pull/12&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/evernote/evernote-sdk-ruby/pull/12&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Mac OS X and Linux on x86_64 with ruby 2.0.0-p195&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
